  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed. The overall credibility posture is assessed as Medium, consistent with a model risk level of 3, medium decision consequence, and medium model influence. Across the 13 factors, 12 meet or exceed their required gradation; the single shortfall in Test conditions is treated as a minor gap managed through documented bounding assumptions and sensitivity analysis.",
