  "signature": "ed25519:9b2e4f7a1c3d5e8f0a2b4c6d8e0f1a3b5c7d9e0f2a4b6c8d0e1f3a5b7c9d0e2f",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver version controlled; regression test suite executed; documented QMS traceability for Ansys Mechanical 2022R2 and in-house pre/post-processing scripts.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA environments (FDA in-house, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) operate under ISO 13485-aligned QMS. Ansys Mechanical 2022R2 is a commercially validated solver with published verification benchmarks. In-house scripts are version-controlled in Git with CI regression testing. Gradation 3 achieved; required Gradation 2 for model risk level 3 with medium decision consequence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification benchmarks covering beam bending, contact mechanics, and large-displacement nonlinear static analysis executed and documented with pass/fail records.",
      "rationale": "Standard ASME V&V 10 benchmark suite for structural mechanics executed against analytical solutions. Contact patch test and cantilever beam convergence verified. All benchmarks pass within 0.5% of analytical reference. Gradation 3 achieved against required Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrating QoI change < 2% between successive refinements; GCI reported for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Four-level mesh refinement study conducted on the pedicle screw shank and rod junction region. GCI for stiffness QoI = 0.8%; for yield force = 1.1%; for force at 40 mm = 0.9%. Richardson extrapolation confirms asymptotic convergence. Final mesh: 187,000 elements (C3D8I and C3D6 types). Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residual norms documented per load step; energy balance checked; solution sensitivity to solver tolerances assessed.",
      "rationale": "Force residual norm < 1e-5 N at each converged increment. Energy balance error < 0.1% across full displacement sweep to 40 mm. Solver tolerance sensitivity study (1e-4 vs 1e-6) shows < 0.3% QoI variation. Required Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent analyst review of model setup; checklist-based QC; documented model review sign-off.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a second analyst at each of the three organizations using a standardized 47-item checklist covering geometry import, material assignment, boundary condition application, contact definition, and load application. All discrepancies resolved prior to result submission. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form assumptions documented and justified; sensitivity of QoIs to key modeling choices (contact formulation, material model, geometric simplification) quantified.",
      "rationale": "The FEA model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity model for Ti-6Al-4V rod and a linear elastic model for UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates. Frictionless penalty contact is used at the screw-rod interface. A sensitivity study varying friction coefficient (0 to 0.3) shows up to 7% variation in yield force QoI, which is within acceptance bounds but not fully characterized across the plausible range of contact conditions. The geometric simplification omitting thread root stress concentrations was justified by the load path analysis, but no explicit uncertainty bound was propagated for this assumption. Model form assessment reaches Gradation 2; required Gradation 3 for this factor given its centrality to the QoIs. This shortfall is acknowledged in the decision record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from traceable coupon testing; geometric inputs verified against CMM measurements; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoIs.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties derived from 15 tensile coupon specimens machined from the same rod lot as test constructs (E = 113.8 ± 1.2 GPa, σ_y = 896 ± 14 MPa). UHMWPE block properties from supplier certificate of conformance, confirmed by three-point bend testing. Screw and rod geometry verified against CMM data for each of the 11 test constructs. Latin hypercube sampling (n=200) used to propagate input uncertainty; 95th percentile QoI band reported. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test constructs from production-representative lot; dimensional inspection completed; traceability to device history record maintained.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-released components (lot traceability maintained). Six constructs tested at Laboratory A (ISO 17025 accredited), five at Laboratory B (ISO 17025 accredited). CMM inspection of each screw and rod prior to assembly; all within drawing tolerances. Inter-laboratory reproducibility assessed; coefficient of variation for stiffness < 3.8%. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions match ASTM F1717 protocol; environmental conditions documented; load application rate and fixture alignment verified.",
      "rationale": "Testing conducted per ASTM F1717-15 at ambient temperature (23 ± 2°C) and humidity (50 ± 10% RH) in accordance with the standard. Displacement rate 25 mm/min; load cell calibration current. Fixture alignment verified with dial indicator prior to each test. Only a single test condition (static compression-bending) was evaluated; dynamic fatigue and torsion conditions are outside this COU scope. Required Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading demonstrably equivalent to physical test setup; fixture compliance characterized and incorporated.",
      "rationale": "Physical fixture stiffness measured experimentally (k_fixture = 42,800 N/mm) and incorporated into FEA as a series spring element. Applied displacement in FEA matches actuator displacement corrected for machine compliance. Screw insertion torque effect on preload characterized by strain gauge measurement on three constructs and replicated in FEA via pre-stress step. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; acceptance threshold pre-specified; results reported per construct and in aggregate.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for each QoI per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4. Stiffness: E/uval = 1.41; Yield force: E/uval = 1.18; Force at 40 mm: E/uval = 1.29. All below the pre-specified threshold of 1.96. Percentage differences: stiffness 8.3%, yield force 5.7%, force at 40 mm 6.1% — all within the 10% acceptance bound. Results reported per construct and in aggregate across both laboratories. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements; traceability to design verification acceptance criteria documented.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the primary outputs required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw systems under ASTM F1717. Each QoI is directly traceable to a design verification acceptance criterion in the device design history file. Clinical relevance: construct stiffness correlates with fusion environment; yield force represents onset of permanent deformation; force at 40 mm represents post-yield reserve capacity. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation scenario (geometry, loading, boundary conditions, material) sufficiently representative of the COU; any gaps between validation scenario and COU documented and bounded.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly replicates the COU: same screw geometry (7.5 mm non-cannulated), same rod diameter (5.5 mm Ti-6Al-4V), same ASTM F1717 loading protocol, same UHMWPE vertebral body surrogates. The COU is the ASTM F1717 test itself, so the validation scenario is the COU. No extrapolation beyond the validated domain is claimed in this submission. Gradation 3 achieved."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-dr-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-cred-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the FEA modeling framework achieves sufficient credibility for its intended use within this COU. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed their required gradation. The single shortfall — Model form (achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3) — reflects incomplete characterization of contact friction uncertainty and thread geometry simplification effects. The team judged this shortfall acceptable on the basis that: (1) the E/uval metric remains well below 1.96 for all QoIs, indicating that any uncharacterized model form error is small relative to experimental uncertainty; (2) the friction sensitivity study bounds the effect to within the 10% acceptance criterion; and (3) the validation scenario is directly equivalent to the COU with no extrapolation. Overall assurance level Medium is declared consistent with model risk level 3, medium decision consequence, and medium model influence. The decision to accept is supported by the weight of evidence across all 13 factors.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
